name: Seattle CityPASS
description:
Seattle CityPASS® — Save 44% or more at Seattle’s five best attractions. 

Discover Seattle's best attractions and enjoy instant delivery of convenient mobile tickets. Perfect for multiple day trips, vacations, or exploring your home city! 

-Space Needle
-Seattle Aquarium 
Plus your choice of admission to 3 of the following attractions:
-Argosy Cruises Harbor Tour 
-Museum of Pop Culture (MoPOP) 
-Woodland Park Zoo
-Chihuly Garden and Glass

Advance reservations may be required at some attractions.

Visit my.citypass.com for up-to-date attraction information including reservations, entry instructions, and helpful tips to plan your visit.

review.name: Not worth it for one day only
review.reviewBody: Only good for one day!  There is too much to do so this is really not a good deal if you have a larger group or small children .  Also does not include the Art museum!  It should be at least two days to use !   Get the 3 pass possibly but you should use it for the Space Needle and the Chihuly museum and gardens, plus the boat tour

review.name: Dont pay full price
review.reviewBody: I always get the City Pass in whatever city I am traveling in. I used Seattles for the Aquarium, Chiluly Garden and Space Needle. Easy to use, great deal!

review.name: City pass
review.reviewBody: Spent a week in I highly recommend getting this pass, it’s with the value. Great options, I dint like heights but could handle the same needle.

review.name: 3 great tours in one
review.reviewBody: We did the sky needle, pike restaurant tour and the harbor cruise.  All were worth it.  The city card gave a nice discount on tours we were going to do,  Saved us some time...

review.name: Definitely a bargain for seeing Seattle
review.reviewBody:
The City Pass is like having someone pay you to see the popular attractions! You can visit the Space Needle twice within 24 hours, and basically anything else included is FREE based on just buying a ticket to the Needle.
This was a great way to enjoy just a few of the things to see and do in Seattle

review.name: THE BEST BANG FOR YOUR BUCK!
review.reviewBody: This, is by far the best kept secret. You get 5 venues to explore at your own pace. Worthy of every penny.  Kinda wish there were more options to choose from, but everything I wanted to see--I saw.

review.name: Good value
review.reviewBody:
Well worth buying one.

You can see a lot in Seattle, and you save money!

Very easy to exchange for tickets and had no issues,

review.name: Wedding in Seattle
review.reviewBody: Great deal ! Pick several options. Included the Aquarium (go early  , less crowd, school kids), Harbor water tour, Space Needle tour (Visit on a clear day, and allowed back within 24 hours for a night tour, but closes early), and a couple Museums(Chihuly and museum of pop culture) Both excellent.

review.name: Good Value for 1st Time Family Visit
review.reviewBody: We thought a lot about getting the City Pass v. paying for individual attractions, but in the end, the City Pass had nearly all of the attractions we were most interested in. Used the maximum number of visits and found it quite easy to exchange for tickets in advance online and make timed reservations for attractions that require those. We used it for the Space Needle, Chihuly Garden and Glass, the Aquarium, the Argosy Harbor Tour, and the Museum of PopCulture.

review.name: Great way to see the city
review.reviewBody: This hit most of the big things we wanted to see in Seattle!  Great value as well.  Easy to use!  No complaints.

itemListElement.name: One-way Private Airport Shuttle to or from Seattle Tacoma Airport

name: One-way Private Airport Shuttle to or from Seattle Tacoma Airport
description: Reach your destination in a stress-free and convenient way! This service provides ground transportation from anywhere in Pacific Northwest Region to and from Seattle Tacoma International Airport. Your professional chauffeur will drive you in a luxury vehicle that is fully licensed, regulated and commercially insured. You can sit back and relax!

review.name: Awful
review.reviewBody:
Driver never showed,
Operator didn’t answer repeatedly phones calls
My family was forced to take a Uber
Spend extra 15 minutes getting a refund 
Expend an extra  2 hours at the airport after 6 hours flight.

review.name: Great ride but…..
review.reviewBody:
We requested a car for 3 people and their luggage. We got a sedan with a trunk that was not big enough for 3 suitcases. Our driver was only expecting 1 person. He said if they knew it was 3, they would have sent a larger car. My reservation shows 3, so not sure where the mix up was. 
We all squished in, with a large suitcase in front seat, and made it home! Our driver was on time, met us in luggage area. Car was clean. Will book with this service again, but not through trip advisor.

review.name: Very Late.
review.reviewBody:
Our reservation was for a 0100 pick up time.
Our driver who was nice did not get there until 0210, being an 1 hour and 10 minutes late.
He stated he only received the pick up notification 2 hours prior. Other than being 1 hour and 10 minutes late everything was fine. Being this late placed a large amount of unnecessary stress along with not being able to eat before having to board our flight. When your going on your first family vacation in 3 years your looking for relaxation and fun not starvation and Stress. Again we did not blame our driver nor did we take our frustrations out on him, we even tipped him for his service.

review.name: Great ride, clear pickup instructions, right on time
review.reviewBody: Arriving on a holiday, we felt we needed to be sure of our ride from the airport to downtown, and I'm really glad we used Seaview airport service; bang on time, super clear pickup instructions, great safe ride into town, with great conversation. Will use again next time I'm in town for sure.

name: Seattle Self-Guided Audio Tour
description:
Learn more about the top 12 tourist attractions in Seattle. Its history, culture, myths, architecture, and other important facts are in this audio commentary.

The top 10 advantages for those who prefer flexibility on their tour.
1. Safe - Not required to download, with just a click of secure access links it can be listened to online on any device.
2. Save - The lowest price in the city.
3. Stories - No imagination stories, only verified information. 
4. Schedule - Listen at your own convenience of time, pace, and location,
5. Select - Preferred languages and attractions.
6. Self-control: No need to be behind someone's instructions in always.
7. Share - with co-travelers in just a click.
8. Soft - Selective crafted words that make you listen again.
9. Simple - Use our personally created itinerary which starts from the city's central station and then gradually moves one by one.
10. Smart - in all aspects.

review.name: Felt VERY let down, beware booking this trip.
review.reviewBody: After reading the reviews on this trip we went ahead and booked. Wish we hadn't, a small old taxi picked us up, 4 adults so was very cramped & boiling hot, driver had very little English, hardly said a word to us. Dropped off at places, no explanation, no info nothing. For the price they charge its daylight robbery,better off just getting your own taxi and going. They advertised Wifi & water neither of which were available. We put in a complaint to the company using WhatsApp,only to then be blocked by them!! All in all a waste of money & waste of a day. BEWARE, I suggest you book independently & not with this company.

review.name: WATCH OUT! this trip isn’t all it seems...
review.reviewBody:
After reading the reviews we had a good feeling that we would enjoy our experience.... WE WERE TOTALLY WRONG! 
BEWARE!!! If you don’t get a good tour guide your experience will be a disaster!! He had ZERO English, gave us no information or knowledge about each location. Didn’t even give us his name!?  
We was not provided what was advertised at all (water). 
It would of been A LOT cheaper and easier to grab a taxi in the street! 
Beware beware beware, we were totally robbed of our money on this tour!

review.name: Trip to Mahaballipuram
review.reviewBody: Our tour operator Mr Ranjith made our family tour so easy and simple that even the children were feeling so confortable and enjoyed the tour.

review.name: Fantastic tour with a great driver
review.reviewBody: Really enjoyed the tour and our driver Mr. Ranjith was great. He spoke English really well and was a very genuine and helpful guy. We visited all of the temples but decided not to do the crocodile stop, that’s the great thing about this tour is you can customise it to suit you. Leaving early is totally the right thing to do as it gets really hot by 10.30 but thankfully we had done a few temples by then. Highly recommend this tour and driver. Highly recommended.

review.name: Best mahabalipuram tour
review.reviewBody: Driver will pick up at the hotel and drive to mahabalipuram, which is around 1 and a half hour from the centre of chennai, a very lovely guide and driver, brings us to many attractions together with the detailed explanation. We gained a lot of knowledge from this tour. Totally would recommend it.

review.name: Customisable convenient tour with excellent services
review.reviewBody: Marvelous sculptures on each rocks that has many stories within it, one of the unforgettable tour experiences

review.name: Mahabalipuram Trip
review.reviewBody: You need to plan it well. This is a bit out of chennai city and will take apprx 2:30 hours from airport. The place is quite old and have a small town around. There are three corners in the place and all corners have some attractions. Keep your car if family is with you, there are public vehicle also available for short travels inside. Overall a place of historical importance and 5-6 hours are required to visit all landmarks.

name: MetroDemic Challenge Game
description:
Engage the brain, get some exercise, and compete to win as you discover amazing secrets within the city.

In the game of MetroDemic, your team has 90-minutes to help our bumbling scientists save thousands of lives from a deadly epidemic!

This is a group-oriented game played on your cell phone alongside a team of 2-4 people. You'll hustle on foot around downtown Bellevue to solve as many challenges as you can in 90 minutes. The challenges are a quirky blend of scavenger hunt clues, pub trivia, and brain puzzles.

itemListElement.name: Join-A-Cruise 3 Night Mother Ship Supported SUP Cruise

name: Join-A-Cruise 3 Night Mother Ship Supported SUP Cruise
description: Sailing and Stand-Up-Paddleboards make a great combination!  Longer downwind/downcurrent paddling options on calm days and/or sailing to a destination to explore at your own pace.  Finish each evening in a different location on a comfortable vessel to fill your belly and rest your bones before the next days adventure.  Spend four days blissfully sailing and paddling around the San Juan Islands on a beautiful & unique catamaran with a good chance of seeing the resident Orca (Killer Whale) pods and other exceptional wildlife in the San Juan Islands.  Three private cabins and a chef make for a relaxing and care free adventure with opportunities for getting off the boat every day to go hiking, exploring or beach combing.

review.name: One Of A Kind
review.reviewBody: Perfect birthday experience with my fiance. The skipper of the boat has a true passion for the ocean and plenty of stories which infuses the experience with an extra layer of significance and enjoyment. As somebody who used to work next to large marine diesel engines the peace and quiet of the electric motors takes it over the top. If you want an adventure that encapsulates all the natural beauty Bellingham has to offer you've found it!

name: Bruce Lee's Chinatown Tour
description: Bruce Lee lived here. His life changed here; but he didn't do it alone. Meet some of his closest friends, his guardians and mentors. Experience the locations of his first school, favorite restaurant and sites where he became a part of this community. Get full access to the 'Do You Know Bruce?' exhibition and the Wing Luke Museum.

name: Touch of Chinatown Seattle
description:
Discover Seattle’s Chinatown, a cultural experience that is unique, historical, educational and fun. Learn about Seattle’s Asian American communities from local guides and experience historic and contemporary Seattle as you stroll through the Chinatown-International District. Admission to the museum can be added at the time of your arrival.

Great for Backpackers, Families and Groups

itemListElement.name: Taste of Pike Place Market Tour

name: Taste of Pike Place Market Tour
description: On this insider's food tour of Seattle's famous Pike Place Market you'll discover hidden food gems from out of the way places as you explore the back alleys and narrow corridors in search of delicious eateries hiding in plain sight. An entertaining local guide will share stories of the Market's cultural history, it's legendary characters and colorful shops in order to enhance your appreciation for this lively historic landmark. This is a small-group tour which allows for a more intimate and enjoyable experience.

review.name: Taste of Pikes Market at its Finest!
review.reviewBody: Jerry was a fantastic historian who toured us around the Pikes Market one early morning.  He was throughly enjoyable and the food…oh the food….so incredibly fantastic!  I am still dreaming of those biscuits, tacos and samosas.  Highly recommend this company — and if you get Jerry - you will be entertained and learn a little about the history of the market and Seattle.

review.name: Fun!
review.reviewBody:
Do NOT eat before this tour! We had a light brunch and we were so stuffed that we couldn’t finish all of the yummy food! I repeat- there is a LOT of food! Our tour guide, Marcia, was very friendly and knowledgeable and made sure that the vegetarians in our party had something to eat. We did the tour with a 3 year old and a 20 month old, which I wouldn’t really recommend as they got bored. 
 We did have some trouble getting on the tour as it was cancelled twice and no one called us and the instructions for the meeting place said to meet at two different places! But we got it all figured out. I recommended that you call ahead to make sure the tour hasn’t been cancelled and to verify the meeting place.

review.name: highly recommended
review.reviewBody: My daughter and i had an awesome time during this tour...although we already visited the market before this tour...we learned a lot from this tour with regard to where to get the best food around the market. Jerry was really sweet and a great tour guide, he made sure everyone's food needs were addressed.

review.name: Food for all
review.reviewBody: Jerry kept the tour exciting and informative, Most people in our group of 12 lived in the area , Learned a lot about Seattle , The market and the sound. The food was plentiful and many options for all food needs. Guide made sure to meet the needs of food allergies on my part and went the extra mile to get a vegetable spring roll since I was allergic to pork made sure to inquire about dill since I am also allergic to that. I would totally recommend this tour to locals and out of towners but would extra recommend if you have out of town  guest for you both to learn a little and have some fun.

review.name: Excellent Pike Place Food Tour
review.reviewBody: We live not far from Pike Place Market and have been there many times.  This tour, led by knowledgeable tour guide Jerry, gave us a totally new appreciation for the market and its foods.  We discovered an  outdoor garden right in the market that we never knew existed and had the chance to sample some great food.  Can't wait to go back with all my new found knowledge. Highly recommend this tour!

review.name: Also known as Taste of Pike Place Food Tour- Great tour!!! (Viator)
review.reviewBody: Our guide Jerry was wonderful!  We had donuts, visited honest biscuits/coffee or tea, vegetable Samosas (Indian food), gelato, a truffle place where we tasted all kinds of interesting yummy products, ellenos yogurt (best yogurt on the the planet), a salmon burger, a yummy taco, beechers herb curds and smoked salmon.  I'm quite sure I forgot a few places and for that I apologize but it was all very interesting and delicious....every last bite and I was very full. Jerry had so many interesting things to tell about the market and its history.  You should book and go!!!

review.name: Bites & Sips, Eats & Treats!
review.reviewBody: Melissa was our tour guide. What a fantastic young woman who introduced us to parts of Pike Place Market that I never knew existed! I have gone on 4 different tours of the market, and each one has unique fun things but it is hard to find new and different items in the market that I'm not aware of. Melissa had at least 5 key points that she pointed out about the history of the market and some of the back stories of the market. She was dedicated to presenting us with a fantastic tour and to providing a top notch tour experience. The food was tasty, there were just two of us on the tour, but that made it even more of an intimate experience. If you want to take a tour with a guide who hasn't just memorized a scrip, but has done her own research as well and has incorporated what she has learned into the tour then Seattle Food Tours with Melissa as your guide won't be a disappointment.

review.name: A bit of history and great food!
review.reviewBody: Melissa was our tour guide and she was fantastic!  I had been to the market a few times on my stops in Seattle, but had never really known the history of Pikes Market.  What a gem it is!  My adult children were with me (who have done food tours in different cities) and they loved it too.  We were able to stop by and talk with the local vendors and try things that I would have never picked out for myself. We fell in love with the truffle oil...and now we have incorporated it into our cooking here at home.  Melissa clearly loves the market and it's people and they know her.  A great way to spend an afternoon!

review.name: Tasting The Market!
review.reviewBody: Our work group got together to take part in the Pike Place Market Food Tour. It was a great time and we all learned new things even though we all live here in Seattle. Our tour guide was Dave (aka Elvis) and he had a great wealth of knowledge about the market history and he was very passionate to share this with the group. I found the samples to be an appropriate size for the tour since we literally sampled from about 10 vendors! I will definitely be back to get more of some of the yummy foods we tried - Samosas, Gelato and Tacos topped my list!

review.name: Being a tourist in your own city is FUN with Seattle Food Tours!
review.reviewBody: Our team did the Seattle Food Tour and our guide was Dave - he was awesome! I learned so much about Pike Place that I never knew and I got to act like a tourist.  Only thing I recommend don't go hungry because the bites are just that "bites." Highly recommend to anyone in or out of towners.

itemListElement.name: West of Seattle's Best Distillery Tours

name: West of Seattle's Best Distillery Tours
description: Enjoy a day touring and tasting at four small-batch craft distillers west of Seattle. Depart from either the Bainbridge Island or Bremerton Ferry Terminal.The tour, tastings and a gourmet picnic lunch are included.

itemListElement.name: Seattle-Tacoma International Airport Arrival Shared Shuttle Service

name: Seattle-Tacoma International Airport Arrival Shared Shuttle Service
description: Save time with a pre-paid arrival transfer from Seattle-Tacoma International Airport to your downtown Seattle hotel or cruise ship terminals and enjoy a stress-free start to your trip without queueing for a taxi. It’s a simple, cost-effective option that’s available seven days a week. Transport is by shared shuttle.

itemListElement.name: Seattle-Tacoma International Arrival Private Shuttle Service

name: Seattle-Tacoma International Arrival Private Shuttle Service
description: Enjoy convenient private transportation between Seattle-Tacoma International Airport and your hotel or cruise ship terminal (pier 66 & pier 91) in the comfort of a private shuttle van.

itemListElement.name: Paddle Board Tour of Lake Union

name: Paddle Board Tour of Lake Union
description: Lake Union is surrounded by some of Seattle's most memorable movie scenes and true Northwest culture. On this scenic paddle tour you will stop to see several sights including Gas Works Park and the famous house boat from Sleepless in Seattle, finished off by water-front food and beverages at a local favorite eatery.

name: 3-Lap Autocross Car Driving Experience
description: Get your adrenaline pumping on this 1.5-hour autocross experience. Drive 3 laps around the course in either a Ferrari 360 Modena, a Ferrari F430, or a Lamborghini Gallardo. Have the thrill of a lifetime in a luxury car.

review.name: Great food and fast cars Motor Valley Italy
review.reviewBody: This was an amazing trip, with every detail taken into account! Excellent food, fantastic guides made the experience even better! Loved the history of the car culture in the area and being able to drive the Ferrari was so fun!  Combine that with outstanding food and restaurant experiences, couldn't have asked for anything more!

review.name: Don't use any other company!!!!
review.reviewBody: Today I drove a Lambo on an autocross track hosted by a different company than Motorsport Lab. Never again will  I pay anyone else but Motorsport Lab. I did the driving experience with Motorsport Lab in Oklahoma City 2 years ago and had the best time ever. The instructors were awesome. The track was way better. The employees made you feel welcome and excited. This other company that I went through today was unprepared, had a tiny track, the instructors weren't very much fun, and they acted like they were doing you a favor by being there. I'll never do this again unless it is Motorsport Lab. This is a real review. Kudos to Motorsport Lab for being the best in the Business that I've experienced !!

review.name: The ride of a lifetime!!
review.reviewBody: I purchased this through Groupon as a birthday gift for my husband, and he said it was the best gift he had ever received.  There were a few hiccups, such as one of the cars needing to have a tire changed and the weather was rainy, but nothing dampened the spirits of all of the people who patiently waited for their turn.  I highly recommend spending the extra money to purchase a video.,.it is a split screen, so you can see the experience from the driver's perspective and from outside of the car.  Of course, there would be extensive paperwork to be completed for insurance purposes...the liability must be insane, given the nature of their business, but this was a painless procedure..I have seen many reviews about the suggestion of an exorbitant tip...a tip is a gratuity, not an obligation.  The instructors certainly earn their tips..they really help to create a fabulous experience, but we did not feel we needed to pay 30% of the total cost.  The instructor seemed satisfied with what we gave him, so I would not let this dissuade you from experiencing the ride of a lifetime.

review.name: We called to cancel and they never returned our call
review.reviewBody: We bought a deal on KSL deals. After finding out about the 25% tip on what the original cost would have been, which means upwards of tipping $159 for what we found out was about 45 seconds to 1 minute of driving time. They also want you to purchase several different insurances, mounting to $300. This so called deal quickly turned into a scam. We also found out that you can’t shift out of second gear and you drive around some cones in a parking lot, not around a racetrack.  We tried the cancel and get a refund, but we didn’t get a callback. This company is horrible and misleading! Don’t waste your money. If you want a real exotic car experience, just rent one for a day. You’ll get way more driving time and actually get to shift out of second gear. Don’t waste your money with this company. Learn from our mistake.

review.name: Exceeded my low expectations
review.reviewBody: I arranged for this experience for my husband and brother for Christmas through Groupon. When I purchased the Groupon voucher, it was my impression that they each would get to drive all three cars. When I confirmed with the Motorsports Lab, it was clear that they would only get to drive one of the vehicles, which was disappointing. Further, the waiver is extensive, aggressive and misleading. I have read a number of reviewers who stopped at the waiver and went no further. As such, I set my expectations low for the actual experience. However, I was pleasantly surprised that the experience itself was very cool, both guys loved it and our families got to explore two supercars with which you usually can't get as up close and personal. The drivers were very supportive and excited and a true value add to whole day.

review.name: Amazing experience.....bucket list!
review.reviewBody:
For a $99 Groupon deal, this was an amazing experience!  I was scheduled to drive the Lambo, but ended up driving the Ferrari as it seemed that more people were waiting on the Lambo and I told the Sherpa I wasn't picky.  He later thanked me for helping with the line "flow".  I've read many negative reviews, but for me this was a great time and i would really like to do it again.  I was not surprised by the short course; after all, I only paid $99 so expecting a full sized track is not realistic.  I also watched the videos and read the information on their website that clearly explained their course setups.

I never expected to be able to drive a Ferrari, so this was AWESOME!  The Sherpa was fantastic and he made the drive much more enjoyable with his directions and comments.  I will always remember the final corner on my last lap.  I started to ease up on the throttle and he said "you don't need to let up, just steer" and he was right!  I would have loved longer or more laps, but it was a blast.....especially for the price!  I tipped the guy for his effort, enthusiasm, and assistance with taking pictures.  He earned a tip!

I see they are coming back to my area in a month or so, and I intend to book this again and drive the Lambo!  Then I will have driven both a Lambo and a Ferrari.....bucket list!

I also wanted to comment on the negative review where the guy said he and a couple of buddies could buy 2 cars and do the same thing.  Yes, I'm sure you could, but have you really thought about what it would take to do that?  Setting up a website, buying 2 super cars, buying the trailer and truck to haul these cars and gear, maintenance on cars, paying for the insurance for this type of business, coordinating all of the different locations around the country and paying the rental fees, lodging, meals, and expenses for the travelling crew, payroll for the crew, etc.  If you think you can do all of this for about $200k, I think you would be wrong.

While I feel bad for the folks who had dates cancelled on them, but in my own experience, this was a great deal and one I will remember for the rest of my life.  I got to actually drive a Ferrari!!!!!  HUGE GRIN!

review.name: It was ok.
review.reviewBody: Driving a Ferrari was a cool experience. However there was some negatives about this. The advertisement talked about an autocross track, but when I went, it was just a very short oval. I expected somewhat of a road course, a few turns, some left, some right, definitely didn’t get that. Don’t get me wrong, the car was fast and it was a cool experience, but driving while constantly turning left, since the “straights” were too short to actually go straight. I basically drove in a giant circle and had to stay in 2nd gear. I would not do this for the regular multi hundred dollars they usually charge. If you don’t get a deal on like groupon like I did, or someway else, it’s not worth the money.

review.name: Awesome experience!
review.reviewBody: Did the Lamborghini 3-lap drive.  Anyone into speed, cars, etc. will love this!  If they had an ATM machine there I’d gone broke.  You can get on the throttle pretty good.  Traction control let’s you not worry about spinning out or otherwise losing control.  Some drivers were creeping around and nothing wrong with that, but if you do it, don’t be intimidated.  And you don’t have to worry about upshifting, downshifting, etc.  you start out in first gear, very quickly shift into 2nd and then you’re done.  Stand on the gas and stand on the brake!  Loved it!

review.name: Fantastic Supercar Experience!
review.reviewBody: This was an early birthday gift from my adorable wife! She's very generous, and very knowledgeable about what I like! First, just a bit of information to clear up, as I've seen this in the negative reviews. It's a Autocross setup, not a race track. The size of the setup will vary from town to town; some larger, some smaller. You get to drive around corners sharply, and get a really good hint of the speed capabilities, but it's not a top speed event. Yes, there is a sheet with additional disclaimers/waivers on it, but with my experience, it was only suggested, and not forced on you. You don't have to pay for them if you don't want to, and you should be careful enough that it won't be a problem. I had no problems contacting them if needed, and the day of the event, I found the folks involved friendly, laid back, and helpful. My "sherpa", the guy in the car with me, was very nice, and in fact, I think we chatted about cars and such a little longer than was necessary (my wife was wondering when we were going to actually start!). The experience itself was a blast! I have a little Miata with a few modifications on it and can zip around corners and take off pretty quickly, so I had a little experience with that. But nothing prepares you for the beautiful sound and indescribable power of the Ferrari 458! It's a beautifully designed, incredibly engineered work of art...basically sex on four wheels! I had a fantastic time, and again, I thank my wonderful wife, and the great staff of Motorsport Lab for the experience.

review.name: Heart Pounding Excitement
review.reviewBody: My wife purchased me a diving experience with a Groupon for a Christmas gift. My first reaction was a very reserved " THATS NICE". Little did I know how much fun and excitement those  3 laps, plus a couple more would be. I had no expectation of driving on a race track or that this would be a driving class. It was several laps around a coned marked track with an observer to coach me along. For a few short minutes I was so totally focused on pushing myself to the limit with the car that I only remembered to breath when I turned back into the "pit" area. It took several minutes to remove the silly grin from my face. For a guy that has done more than his share of exciting stuff in 60 years, that is saying allot. If you get the chance to do this jump on it. And remember, drive it like you stole it.

name: The Seattle Kush Tour
description:
The Kush Tour is Seattle's Cannabis Tour!  Our tour is an educational experience that takes you behind the scenes of Seattle’s Cannabis Culture and the working Marijuana industry! Learn how artists create hand-blown pipes, how to grow Cannabis on a commercial scale, and how Cannabis is processed into the products found in retail stores.  We have operated Cannabis Tours for 2.5 years and would like to take you on a quality Seattle adventure! 

*As seen on the History Channel.

name: Bicycle History and Brewery Tour
description:
• The Only Bicycle History and Brewery Tour in Washington 
 • A guided 4-hour, five-mile bicycle ride throughout downtown Tacoma
 • A visit to four breweries and a whiskey distillery (generous samples included)
 • An offbeat history of the legends and lores that built the City of Destiny (Tacoma)

name: Seattle City Tour 3-Hours (Private Tour)
description:
We specialized in private experiences for small groups. 

During the tour, we will make three stops in places of tourist importance. The first stop will be the Pioneer Square neighborhood located in the historic district of the old metropolis where we will visit the origins of Seattle on a walk suitable for the whole family and full of history, architecture, and photography.

We will continue to the Ballard Locks for our second stop. We will see the boats enter and leave the Pacific Ocean to the lakes surrounding the city.

Finally, we will end with one of the most impressive panoramic views before ending the tour where we can take some of the best photos of the city center. The tour ends at the Space Needle, Pike Place Market, or returned to your hotel. It is generally a 3-hour tour but it can be extended if the group wishes. This tour is highly recommended for children and adults of all ages.

IMPORTANT: The tour is in English but it can be arranged in Spanish.

review.name: Incrível
review.reviewBody: Foi incrível! O Mario nos mostrou um lado de Seattle que não conheceríamos sem sua ajuda! Os arredores da cidade! Super indico!’

review.name: Un City tour excelente para volver a hacer
review.reviewBody: El tour fue muy completo, Mario es guía además de tener muchos conocimientos es muy ameno, agradable y considerado siempre atento a todos los detalles

review.name: Conocimos todo lo principal que queríamos conocer en Seattle
review.reviewBody: Muy buen recorrido, muy ameno y conocimos un montón, Mario siempre muy complaciente, además nos toco un día maravilloso así es que el tour fue Top.

review.name: Good Eats
review.reviewBody: Chef Scott was awesome and very knowledgeable. We had so many snacks along the way we didn’t need lunch😊 Tour itself was very interesting and we saw so many places. We went back the next day to buy more goodie’s!

review.name: Perfect private tour of Seattle!
review.reviewBody: Mario was amazing! He picked us up at our downtown hotel and was exactly on time. He is friendly, extremely knowledgeable about the city and it's history and made our tour fun and tailored to our family and our interests! In the days of social media, I also have to mention his photography skills for the posts after the tour! 100% Thank you Mario!

review.name: Great tour
review.reviewBody: Mario did a great job with showing hidden gems in the city. He showed us places we would not have gone to on our own.Mario was very friendly and helped with everything we needed and made sure we didn’t waste time in traffic, etc.

review.name: Enjoyable 3 Hours
review.reviewBody: Interesting itinerary tailored to our interests. Mario is knowledgeable, experienced and has engaging personality.

review.name: Must do this tour!
review.reviewBody: We thoroughly enjoyed our tour of Seattle. James was our tour guide and he was fantastic.  He was informative, interesting and you could tell he was passionate about his job and his city.   Highly recommend you take this tour - convenient pick up at our hotel, several great stops and drop off at the market so we could continue to explore this great city!

review.name: Great tour of Seattle
review.reviewBody: What a great tour we had with Mario.  It was the perfect way to see Seattle.  Mario took us to very interesting places and had so much information, history and facts about Seattle.  He met us in time and discussed what was of interest to us then took us to places and told us stories about the area. Took pics for us, then gave us suggestions on where we could go on our own.  Saved us money by helping us with subway instead of Uber.  He dropped our bags off first from airport so we could tour around without our baggage.  Yes I would highly recommend booking Mario when you are in Seattle area.  He speaks 4 languages and is honest.

review.name: Fantastic tour (and guide)
review.reviewBody: What a great tour. And what a great tour guide. Very knowledgeable, very accommodating, and very nice. We could not have been happier about the experience. We learned a ton, saw a ton, and got great recommendations. A+++.

itemListElement.name: Zipline Canopy Tour with Transportation from Seattle

name: Zipline Canopy Tour with Transportation from Seattle
description: Let us take care of your transport from Seattle hotels with this inclusive zipline tour. Located on historic Kristoferson Farm on Camano Island, our canopy tour is a forest experience like nothing else! Walking between the zips, you will learn about the fascinating nature, wildlife and the rich history of the land. Then you will see an exhilarating new view as you zip between the trees! Enjoy an unforgettable time as your guides (certified to ACCT standards and first aid/CPR trained) take care of clip-ins and all the other details.

review.name: Just do it
review.reviewBody:
54 yo mom (that’d be me) and 10 yo daughter. Terrified. We had a BLAST. Still terrified until about the 3rd line then it was like, “well we’re still alive. Statistically likely that we’ll remain alive.” Our guides Adrian and Maddie were excellent and fun. 

About 3 hours of terror and fun. Worth the money. 

Get the GoPro; worth it.  

We’d do it again

review.name: Canopy Tour Zipline was AMAZING!!
review.reviewBody:
My husband & I, along with our two best friends, traveled to Seattle for 5 days of fun!  One of those days included the Canopy Zipline tour.  We were picked up in the Zipline shuttle, and immediately upon boarding the shuttle, we were offered coffee and homemade blueberry/lavender muffins. Off to a great start!
Once at the farm, we filled out our forms and then went to the barn to be weighed and fitted into our harnesses and helmets.  Our tour guides Colin and Jenna were outstanding!  They put everyone at ease and made the entire experience very easy and memorable.  Colin has the best attitude and sense of humor - he was fabulous!  There were 4 children in our group of zipliners, and both guides were awesome with everyone - kids and adults alike.  We were amazed at their ability to easily remember the names of all 9 people who were "zipping!"
Riding the ziplines was so thrilling!!   A little bit scary at first, but not too bad ... such a fun, free feeling as you're zipping through the beautiful, green scenery with the cool breeze on your face.  Coming from Las Vegas, we really appreciated teh cooler weather and beautiful, green scenery.
There was one point where we stopped to have some cold lavender lemonade in between zip lines, and took some fun selfies with the Canopy Tours selfie camera.
We also ordered the lunch to eat at the farm after we were done zipping.  It was a nice sized salad, a huge 1/2 sandwich and a very delicious cookie.
Afterwards we purchased a couple of items from the gift shop.  The lady was super friendly, helping us try on sweatshirts and choosing the perfect size.
I would absolutely recommend Canopy Tours - it was a tremendous experience from beginning to end!

review.name: Brilliant Reunion activity!
review.reviewBody: Zipping has been on my bucket list for some time, and when it became part of Reunion Weekend, it was time to step up and be counted! (Although I must say I have bragging rights on this one!) Everyone at Canopy Tours seemed to know just how much coddling this (ahem, old) newbie needed - didn't have traffic worries because I relaxed on the shuttle. The zip guides and other guests were all super friendly and encouraging, (thank you for the tip on how to cross the bridge!) and who can beat this location? Bonus: perfect weather day, and a peek at the challenge course tucked discreetly into nature. I can't wait to bring folks here for Team Building or Zipping!

review.name: Outing with Hotel Family
review.reviewBody: Took the team out for a great team building experience. The trip out to Camano Island was fun and the driver had some insightful stories to tell. The overall service was great and the help ease the nerves of one of our colleagues who was scared of heights. Definitely would recommend, also to note it would be best to also add the lunch feature as the sandwiches were delicious.

review.name: Amazing Experience for Work Event
review.reviewBody:
I coordinated a tour with Canopy Tours NW as a fun/unique event for a company retreat for US and international guests.  Participants varied in age, and everyone had a wonderful time!  It was definitely a highlight of the corporate retreat and was a great way for employees to get to know each other and support one another.  Planning our outing was a breeze, Mona Campbell did a wonderful job helping me coordinate the event and was very available and accommodating to our group's needs.  We set-up group transportation to/from the farm from our hotel in Seattle, this was a breeze and both drivers (Dave Baggenstos and Jacob Newman) were on time to take us there and back, no issues whatsoever.

The actual ziplining experience was awesome, the length of time of the tour and the amount of lines to zip was perfect, no one lost interest!  It was a perfect day (which helped), and all of the instructors were friendly.  They made sure we felt safe and comfortable throughout the whole tour.  I'd definitely recommend this to anyone looking to book a fun event for family, friends, or in my case, coworkers.  It's great for team-building and a unique opportunity for everyone to experience and share afterwards!

itemListElement.name: Seattle Sailing Lesson on Lake Union

name: Seattle Sailing Lesson on Lake Union
description: Two-hour sailing lesson on Lake Union in Seattle with a professional captain to show you the ropes on a small, exciting boat that is electric and eco-friendly. Set sail and enjoy the fantastic views from the water with a small-group and personal attention right in the heart of Seattle. This introduction to sailing class will provide for those with a sense of adventure and cover the basics, safety, and sailing theory. The lesson is easy to fit in your schedule with multiple departure offered throughout the day to choose from.

name: 1.5-Hour Sail on Seattle's Historic 1926 Schooner
description:
Step back in history aboard the historic Lavengro, a 1926 wooden gaff rigged schooner.  A great boat for experiencing what sailing was like in the last century. This is a great excursion for a romantic evening or the whole family.

Watch seaplane take-offs and landings up close and see the iconic Space Needle, Gas Works Park, the Fremont Bridge, and St. Marks Cathedral. Cruise past dozens of floating homes including the 'Sleepless in Seattle' floating home. See hundreds of boats from classic cruisers to modern mega yachts.

This is a 1.5-hour shared experience with a limited capacity of 22 guests. There is plenty of space on the boat to spread out and enjoy the view, or hop in with your captain and crew to learn how to sail this historic vessel.

name: Trace Market
description: TRACE Market is an artisanal, fast, local, and planet friendly restaurant, located in the heart of downtown at W Seattle. The restaurant's market-driven menus are inspired by the regional bounty of the Pacific Northwest and are expertly crafted by Chef Ross Lewis. TRACE Market offers dine-in, take-out, and grab-and-go options for breakfast, brunch, and lunch daily.
